    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Shrub or small tree with brownish-greyish, rough bark and often multiple stems. Leaves leathery and elliptical with strong venation and sunken central vein. Upper surface dull green, lower surface paler greyish-white and velvety, margins of leaf minutely toothed. Smells strongly of camphor.</p><p>Flower heads in terminal sprays, individual flowers creamy white and covered with white woolly hairs. Fruit a small nut covered in woolly hair, the heads resembling balls of cotton wool.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_9825",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Growing to about 5 m height. Leaves 40-80 mm long.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_9826",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to South Africa.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> About Saldanha Bay to southern KwaZulu-Natal.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_9827",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Coastal species that can occur almost down to high-water mark. A versatile plant used in traditional medicine for respiratory and digestive conditions and as a source of perfume and insect repellent. The wood is also hard and durable and can be used for fence posts, furniture or even musical instruments.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_9828",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_9829",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Flowers December to April. &nbsp;Plants are dioecious.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_9830",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>The Camphor bush <i>T. camphoratus</i> is similar and has an overlapping rang but also occurs far inland across eastern and northern parts of South Africa and northwards to Somalia. It grows larger, to 6 m, and has longer pointed leaves up to150 mm long.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_9831",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        }
    ],
